&lt/body><br>
&lt/html><br>
          <hr>
          
Q4. Describe the process of adding a CSS file and JavaScript file to HTML?<br>

To add a CSS file:<br>

- Create a separate file with a .css extension (e.g., styles.css).<br>
- In the HTML document, add a &ltlink> tag in the &lthead> section, pointing to the CSS file: &ltlink rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="styles.css"><br>

To add a JavaScript file:<br>

- Create a separate file with a .js extension (e.g., script.js).<br>
- In the HTML document, add a &ltscript> tag in the &lthead> or &ltbody> section, pointing to the JavaScript file: &ltscript src="script.js">&lt/script><br>
          <br>
Alternatively, you can also embed CSS and JavaScript code directly within the HTML document using &ltstyle> and &ltscript> tags, respectively. However, separating them into external files is a best practice for organization and maintainability.
