Q1. Write a short note on creation of basic form and its elements?<br>

A basic form in HTML consists of a &ltform> element, which contains various input elements like text fields, checkboxes, radio buttons, and submit buttons. <br>
The &ltform> element has an action attribute specifying where to send the form data and a method attribute specifying the submission method (GET or POST).<br>
              <hr>
Q2. Discuss form tag attributes?<br>

Common form tag attributes include:<br>

- action: specifies where to send the form data<br>
- method: specifies the submission method (GET or POST)<br>
- enctype: specifies the encoding type for file uploads<br>
- name: specifies the form name<br>
- id: specifies the form ID<br>
- class: specifies the form class<br>
- style: specifies the form styles<br>
              <hr>
Q3. List out various types of input text boxes?<br>

Various types of input text boxes include:<br>

- Text input (type="text")<br>
- Password input (type="password")<br>
- Email input (type="email")<br>
- Number input (type="number")<br>
- Date input (type="date")<br>
- Time input (type="time")<br>
- File input (type="file")<br>
              <hr>
Q4. What is placeholder text?<br>

Placeholder text is a hint or example text displayed in an input field to guide users on what to enter. <br>
It disappears when the user starts typing.<br>
              <hr>
Q5. Discuss checkbox, radio, and select option drop-down elements?<br>

- Checkboxes: allow multiple selections<br>
- Radio buttons: allow single selection<br>
- Select option drop-downs: allow single selection from a list<br>
- Checkboxes and radio buttons use the &ltinput> element with type attributes<br>
- Select option drop-downs use the &ltselect> element with &ltoption> elements<br>
